    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter">
                <head type="title">Miklós Oláh to King Ferdinand I (Vienna, 28 June 1552)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p>1. Since at Maximilian’s order someone had to be sent to Mihály Perényi’s
                            wedding on his behalf, he sent Mihály Révay, who also went to Košice on
                            his way home, and King Ferdinand I will learn from Ferenc Révay’s
                            attached letter what he heard from György Serédy. 2. In addition, the
                            Provost of Leles was also here, and he says that Petrovics sent three
                            legates to Poland recently, but they made a detour to Lelesz, and one of
                            them, called Ördög, talked to the Provost, but he could not find out why
                            they were going to Poland.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p>Sacratissime Rex, Domine Clementissime, orationum devotarum et fidelium
                    servitiorum humillimam commendationem!</p>
                <p>[1.] Cum his diebus ex mandato serenissimi regis
                        <persName>Maximiliani</persName>, domini mei clementissimi ad nuptias
                    magnifici <persName>Michaelis de Peren</persName><note type="critic">Mihály
                        Perényi (†1557), <hi rend="italic">ispán</hi> of Zemplén married Lukács
                        Székely’s daughter, Katalin Székely of Ormosd and Kövend (†1587) on 3 July,
                        1552, see <hi rend="smallcap">Szabó–Hanák</hi> 2021, 125; and <hi
                            rend="smallcap">Kovachich</hi> 1798, 93.</note> aliquem nuntium de more,
                    nomine Vestrae Maiestatis suaeque serenitatis deligere me oportuisset, nemineque
                    alio sese tum offerente egregium <persName>Michaelem de Rewa</persName>,<note
                        type="critic">Mihály Révay.</note> filium videlicet domini
                        <persName>Reway</persName><note type="critic">Ferenc Révay.</note> in aulam
                    Vestrae Maiestatis commendatum eo dimisissem. Isque in reditu ex illis partibus
                        <placeName>Cassowiam</placeName><note type="critic">Košice.</note>
                    divertisset, ibi quae ex domino <persName>Georgio Seredy</persName><note
                        type="critic">György Serédy.</note> intellexit, cognoscet Maiestas Vestra ex
                    hac praesentibus inclusa scriptura, manu eiusdem <persName>Michaelis de
                        Rewa</persName> confecta,<note type="critic">For a copy of Révay’s report,
                        see ÖStA HHStA UA AA Fasc. 66. Konv. A. fol. 112–113.</note> quae mihi pro
                    mei officii ratione ad Maiestatem Vestram visa sunt perscribenda.</p>
                <p>[2.] Venit praeterea hodie huc <persName>praepositus de
                        Lelez</persName><note type="critic">György Bódy was Provost of Leles between
                        1547 and 1557, see <hi rend="smallcap">Pankovics</hi> 2013, 21.</note>
                    narravitque mihi proximis diebus ex Transsylvania tres nuntios in
                        <placeName>Poloniam</placeName> ad <persName>Petrowyth</persName><note
                        type="critic">Péter Petrovics.</note> euntes in itinere ad
                        <placeName>Lelez</placeName><note type="critic">Leles.</note> divertisse, et
                    ex his unum cognomento <persName>Ewrdeg</persName>,<note type="critic">Ördög or
                        Eördögh. We do not know him more closely.</note> cuius frater superiori anno
                    in Transylvania vivente adhuc <persName>Fratre Georgio</persName><note
                        type="critic">George Martinuzzi was killed on 17 December, 1551.</note>
                    fuerat interfectus, in arcem ad ipsum praepositum ascendisse, secumque esse
                    collocutum, sed se nulla ratione elicere ab eo potuisse, quid negotii acturi in
                        <placeName>Poloniam</placeName> proficiscantur. Quod item ad Vestram
                    Maiestatem volui pro debito officii mei perscribere. Servet eandem summus Deus
                    felicem et incolumem quam ditutissime. </p>
                <p><placeName>Viennae</placeName> die decimo octavo mensis Iulii anno
                    Domini 1552.</p>
                <p>
                    <add corresp="Olahus" type="insert">Eiusdem Sacratissimae Maiestatis Vestrae
                        fidelis et oboediens servitor</add>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <seg type="signature"><add corresp="Olahus" type="insert">Agriensis etc. manu
                            propria</add></seg>
                </p>
                <pb/>
            </div>
            <div style="handwritten" type="verso">
                <head>On the outer side:</head>
                <p>Sacratissimae Romanorum Hungariae Bohemiae etc. regiae maiestati
                    domino, domino meo clementissimo.</p>
                
            </div>
